===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|はやぶさ|yomi=k|alt=鶻,鸇}}
{{swp|ja:ハヤブサ}}
Attested in early {{inh|ja|ojp|-}} texts: the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' (712) as {{lang|ja|波夜夫佐}} and the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' (720) as {{lang|ja|破夜歩佐}}.<ref name="KDJ2O"/><ref name="JDB">{{R:JDB|pages=596-597}}</ref>

Further etymology is {{unc|ja|nocap=1}}; a popular etymology is that it derives from a corruption of {{ja-com|早|はや-|t1=[[early]]; [[fast]]|翼|つばさ|t2=[[wing]] ([[bird]])}}.<ref name="KDJ2O"/>

